            "id": 1,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "Short vowels and other diacritics are not part of written Arabic scripts . <S>",
            "relation": "BACKGROUND"
        },
        {
            "id": 2,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Exceptions are made for important political and religious texts and in scripts for beginning students of Arabic . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 3,
            "parent": 1,
            "text": "Script without diacritics have considerable ambiguity ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 4,
            "parent": 3,
            "text": "because many words with different diacritic patterns appear identical in a diacritic-less setting . <S>",
            "relation": "CAUSE-RESULT-REASON"
        },
        {
            "id": 5,
            "parent": 0,
            "text": "We propose in this paper a maximum entropy approach ",
            "relation": "ROOT"
        },
        {
            "id": 6,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "for restoring diacritics in a document . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 7,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "The approach can easily integrate and make effective use of diverse types of information ; ",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 8,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "the model we propose integrates a wide array of lexical , segmentbased and part-of-speech tag features . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 9,
            "parent": 7,
            "text": "The combination of these feature types leads to a state-of-the-art diacritization model . <S>",
            "relation": "ELABORATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 10,
            "parent": 11,
            "text": "Using a publicly available corpus ( LDC's Arabic Treebank Part 3 ) , ",
            "relation": "MANNER-MEANS"
        },
        {
            "id": 11,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "we achieve a diacritic error rate of 5.1 % , a segment error rate 8.5 % , and a word error rate of 17.3 % . <S>",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        },
        {
            "id": 12,
            "parent": 5,
            "text": "In case-ending-less setting , we obtain a diacritic error rate of 2.2 % , a segment error rate 4.0 % , and a word error rate of 7.2 % . <S>",
            "relation": "EVALUATION"
        }
    ]
}